- "Embarkation point" is the location from which the passengers boarded the ship.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM passengers p
WHERE p.fare > 50 AND p.pclass = 1 AND p.survived = 'Yes';

external_knowledge:
- "male passengers over 18" refers to adult male passengers;
- "first class" refers to passengers in the highest class of travel;
- "paid more than the average fare" means the fare is greater than the average fare for first class passengers;
- "has family members on board" is determined by the number of related passengers found in the `PassengerFamily` CTE.
